# SwiftUI DesignSystem views (iOS 2026 template)

- **Always** add a `#Preview` for every DesignSystem view so components are visible in Xcode’s canvas and stay visually regressable.
- **Do not** introduce a view model (`ObservableObject`, `@Observable` UI state types, or `*ViewModel`) for DesignSystem views. Keep them **presentational**: parameters, bindings, and simple private helpers only.

```swift
// ✅ GOOD — preview + stateless/presentational API
struct DSPrimaryButton: View {
    let title: String
    let action: () -> Void

    var body: some View { /* ... */ }
}

#Preview {
    DSPrimaryButton(title: "Continue") { }
}

// ❌ BAD — DesignSystem coupled to a ViewModel
@Observable
final class DSPrimaryButtonViewModel { /* ... */ }
```
